      "text": "Logic Design Flow:\nStep 1. Content collection\nUpload materials-> preprocessing->normalization\nRemove noise, Extracts structure( chapters, headings)\nStep2: Concept Extraction\nText->NLP Analyzer->Concept Graph\nidentifies : Defintion, Relationships, Dependecies\nExamples: Algebra->Equations->Solving methods\nSteps 3: Learning Profile Initilization:\nNew user-> Default learning style-> Diagnostic quiz\nCreates: Baseline knowledge score, Preferred learning style( visual, auditory\n\nStep 4: Question Generation Flow\nConcept->Difficulty selection->LLM prompt-> Quiz creation\nAdaptive examples: \nBeginner->defin MCQs, Intermediate-> appln problems, Advnced->scenario based questions\n\nStep 5: Answer Evaluation\nStudent anser->Auto grading->concept score update\nUpdates: Accuracy, Confifence score, Response time\n\nStep 6: Adaptive Explation EngineLow score-> Alternate explanation-> New practice\n Explanation styles:\nVisual->Diagms and charts, Auditory-> analogies stores, kinesthetic-> step by step problem solving\n\nStep 7: Progress Tracking & Persistence\n Performance metrics -> SQ;ote database\n Metric & Purpose ( Accuracy->Mastery, Time-> Engagement, Attempts-> Difficytly tuninng\nStep 8: Spaced Repetition Schedulr:\n  Master-> Review after longer gap\n  Struggling-> Review sooner\n  Uses: Leitner-style buckets, Performanc- based intervals\nStep 9: Continuous Feedbacl Loop:\n Study->Test->Analyze->Adapt->Reschedule\nThis loop runs continuosle, making learning,\nEffiecient and Engaging\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Logic Design Flow:\nStep 1. Content collection\nUpload materials-> preprocessing->normalization\nRemove noise, Extracts structure( chapters, headings)\nStep2: Concept Extraction\nText->NLP Analyzer->Concept Graph\nidentifies : Defintion, Relationships, Dependecies\nExamples: Algebra->Equations->Solving methods\nSteps 3: Learning Profile Initilization:\nNew user-> Default learning style-> Diagnostic quiz\nCreates: Baseline knowledge score, Preferred learning style( visual, auditory\n\nStep 4: Question Generation Flow\nConcept->Difficulty selection->LLM prompt-> Quiz creation\nAdaptive examples: \nBeginner->defin MCQs, Intermediate-> appln problems, Advnced->scenario based questions\n\nStep 5: Answer Evaluation\nStudent anser->Auto grading->concept score update\nUpdates: Accuracy, Confifence score, Response time\n\nStep 6: Adaptive Explation EngineLow score-> Alternate explanation-> New practice\n Explanation styles:\nVisual->Diagms and charts, Auditory-> analogies stores, kinesthetic-> step by step problem solving\n\nStep 7: Progress Tracking & Persistence\n Performance metrics -> SQ;ote database\n Metric & Purpose ( Accuracy->Mastery, Time-> Engagement, Attempts-> Difficytly tuninng\nStep 8: Spaced Repetition Schedulr:\n  Master-> Review after longer gap\n  Struggling-> Review sooner\n  Uses: Leitner-style buckets, Performanc- based intervals\nStep 9: Continuous Feedbacl Loop:\n Study->Test->Analyze->Adapt->Reschedule\nThis loop runs continuosle, making learning,\nEffiecient and Engaging\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
